<br>
Hm, i dunnno... too long of an explanation.<br>
<br>
Best, shortest way I can state my opinion(though stated as fact or definition or something) is:<br>
<br>
There should never be a situation where a mage would rather be able to summon a beastlord pet than one of his own pets.<br>
<br>
I do not like the idea of BL pets coming close to our pets. I feel that the EoT pet is way too close as it is.<br>
<br>
However, if the BL pet were to be upgraded close to our pets, it would probably be something I'd deal with. I guess ever since they made our pets neutral to mobs, it's been really easy to roll with the punches of class balancing ^_^<br>
<br>
What I would never be able to deal with, is if I'm fighting a certain mob, and I find myself thinking 'i wish i had a warder instead of my 3 slightly specialized pets'<br>
<br>
I'd probably just start a SK and loot uber loot from FD in the corner, or quit entirely. More likely, I predict I'd quit entirely. There's some primal instinct in man, equally prevalent on all levels of thought not exluding relaxing things like video games, that causes him to react extremely violently to the breaking of principles pre-established in his mind... such as waking one day waking up and finding that mage pets are not the best. The breakage of principle! Ahh! violent psychological reaction! quit EQ !.... In the matrix, they did not free a mind after a certain age. That's all I'll say.<br>
<br>
Yeah, perhaps that creative argument got a bit absurd, but something to chew on :p <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=109465>~Krilen</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=zyrexxshadowfyre>Zyrexx Shadowfyre</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 319<br> <font color=#333333>(10/1/02 6:21:43 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=363.topic&index=24>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_mad.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Oh god, not again...</span><hr size=1> ****Beastlord without pet outdamaging a mage without pet?****<br>
<br>
I sure as hell would not mind this.<br>
<br>
Say your teamed with a Beast Lord, some how both your pets die would you rather:<br>
<br>
A) be the bigger damage dealer getting the agro and getting yourself shredded to tiny little bits<br>
<br>
 or<br>
<br>
B) let the Beast Lord with his better HP, AC and Defence abilities get the attention allowing you to stager your nukes so you both will survive<br>
<br>
But then we would have to know how would the Beast Lord out damage us ? <br>
<br>
In a short fight with a resonably tough apponent with out mega hit points a nuker will almost allways come out on top (Not taking into account Haste items, Spells or Abilities). A melee doing nuke damage in a short ammount of time, with out a special ability like Back Stab or Mega Archery AAs, would be over powered.<br>
<br>
In a long fight, with an apponent with alot more hit points the melee should out damage a nuker as the nuker will have spent most of their mana before the fight end (Not taking into account Mana regen spells / abilities). Long term damage by magic is the realm of DoTers (Yes we have some DoTs but their not like a Necro or Shammies).<br>
<br>
If right now we out damage a Beast Lord in both Short and Long fights with out a pet then there is really somthing wrong.  <p><center><TABLE><TR>
