<br>
Mages nuke, their pets tank.<br>
<br>
Beastlords melee, they tank.<br>
<br>
Therefore mage pet defense &gt; beastlord pet defense.<br>
<br>
But beastlord pet offense &gt;= mage pet offense(more than Gvoc pet, near or at epic damage).  <br>
<br>
Mages retain the best overall pets, beastlords become something other than a bad joke.<br>
<br>
<br>
Of course, none of this matters because VI doesn't care a whit about what a bunch of whiners on a messageboard think. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=wezloc>WEZLOC</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 867<br> <font color=#333333>(10/1/02 10:08:44 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=363.topic&index=26>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  hehe</span><hr size=1> Mages pet tank because mages do not have root so there is no other options but to let the pet tank. BL have a option mages do not. Also I do not use my nukes to kill mobs. That isn't the way that I play and most mages do not play that way either. If a GV Earth needs say 130% health to solo kill a mob I will normally nuke enough to ensure that pet finishes with 40% life. I do not chain cast and I invest items and gear in my pets so it isn't worthwhile for me to recast. I have epic now and for most things that I solo it does 70% of the damage to most of the things I kill. In a group it is near half my total damage.<br>
<br>
What alot of people miss is Verant is against soloing. Alot of the beastlord concerns are based on solo encounters. In a experience group where tanks are present all pets revert to living damage dots. Now under those conditions you are saying that mages should have a weaker damage pet then a hybrid class?<br>
<br>
Beastlords have skipped right over necros and are going after what belongs to the mage.<br>
<br>
GV Earth = Mage Version or Root. It has low ac so that it will get hit alot causing mobs to take more damage via a damage shield. To offset this they gave this pet the most hps.<br>
<br>
GVFire = A joke<br>
<br>
GV Water = Best damage pet in the game. In a group setting it gives the mage the option to go offensive since VI realizes even tho BLs do not that tanking means nothing in a normal experience group where a tank is present. This is the second worse tank pet that we have however I used this pet at 60 to solo until i got epic. With summoned armor ect....it tanks ok and the damage it does from nukes and melee while having the added benefit to get in some backstabs while the mob is running away helps alot.  Also it regens the fastest of all pets so the lower hps are offset somewhat by recovering from a encounter faster.<br>
<br>
GV Air = The all around pet. It is good against caster mobs because of the stun. It is good against melee mobs because of the stun. It tanks the best but has far less hps then GVE. It has damage equal to GV Earth but fewer hps with better damage mitigation.<br>
<br>
This shows clearly that we are a specialized pet class. We move more into that area as we lvl up. A beastlord pet being on par with any one of these pets isn't ok. The reason is the pets are specialized and take into account what enviornment a mage would use them in. Beastlords were suppose to have pets on par with lvl 49 necros.  Necros are suppose to be a better pet class then them. <br>
<br>
60% of what mages offer comes through their pet. Mod Rods, Summoned focus items, throwing daggers, and summoned food are secondary skills to help round the class out, however the main ability that a mage brings to the table the ability to summon a pet for all occasions and it will never be out done in it's specialized field.<br>
<br>
Beastlords have a TON of utility to offer along with their pet.  50% slow from that mega easy epic as well as 50% slow from the lvl 60 spell is a great benefit.  You think the lvl 60 slow is rare well talk to some mages about the lvl 60 pet heal. You have a ton of utility to offer a group where as a mage offers for the most part damage with limited utility. So why would it be fair for a class like BST which have extremely high utility to have a pet that is on par with mage pets in damage considering how limited we are on utility?<br>
<br>
Wezloc <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=wezloc>WEZLOC</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 868<br> <font color=#333333>(10/1/02 10:20:45 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=363.topic&index=27>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  lol mages are on par with wizards? Pass the bowl please</span><hr size=1> Znail<br>
<br>
Your comparison is very weak. The reason is because mages are FAR behind wizards in nuking. I will explain it out for ya since you don't understand....<br>
<br>
Wizards have......<br>
<br>
Lower resist checks when casting nukes<br>
Wizard nukes have a lower resist rate overall<br>
Wizards have unresistable lure nukes <br>
Wizards have bane nukes<br>
Wizards have nukes that cover all resistances<br>
Wizards can nuke quick for small but good damage or<br>
Wizards can nuke a little slower for large amounts of damage and they can do it with fire/cold/magic.<br>
There is NOT ONE MOB in the game that a wizard can not land a nuke on due to the change to lures<br>
Wizard nukes OVERALL are superior to mage nukes in damage, cast time, ratio, mana cost.<br>
Wizard can crit without the need of AA<br>
Wizards have manaburn<br>
<br>
<br>
This is what makes wizards far superior to mages in nuking. Yes Fire Bolt of Tallon is 3.75 but has line of sight issues and is still weaker then Ice Spear which has no line of sight issues, cost less mana, does the same damage in less then half the time and I might add it is soon to be two expansions old. Also a wizard is going to land Ice Spear more consistantly for full damage and with less resist then a mage with Fire Bolt. So looking at the ratio on nukes doesn't tell the entire story. Mages should dominate pets like wizards dominate nuking. If anyone believes wizards are not far and away the most dominate nuking class in the game they should go back to AO.<br>
<br>
It is like saying well the new beastlord pet hits for 69 at 60 (which it does) so it is on par with the lvl 60 mage GV Water pet which only hits for 68. See how flawed your logic is?<br>
<br>
Wezloc<br>
